====Vowels====
{{Sinhala Mi≈õra set vowels}}

There are six additional vocalic diacritics in the ''mi≈õra'' alphabet. The two [[diphthong]]s are quite common, while the &quot;syllabic&quot; ·πõ is much rarer, and the &quot;syllabic&quot; ·∏∑ is all but obsolete. The latter are almost exclusively found in loanwords from Sanskrit.&lt;ref name=&quot;Matzel8&quot;&gt;Matzel (1983), p. 8&lt;/ref&gt;

The ''mi≈õra'' {{angle bracket|·πõ}} can also be written with ''≈õuddha'' {{angle bracket|r}}+{{angle bracket|u}} or {{angle bracket|u}}+{{angle bracket|r}}, which corresponds to the actual [[pronunciation]]. The ''mi≈õra'' syllabic {{angle bracket|·∏∑}} is obsolete, but can be rendered by ''≈õuddha'' {{angle bracket|l}}+{{angle bracket|i}}.&lt;ref name=&quot;Matzel14&quot;&gt;Matzel (1983), p. 14&lt;/ref&gt; Mi≈õra {{angle bracket|au}} is rendered as  ''≈õuddha'' {{angle bracket|awu}}, ''mi≈õra'' {{angle bracket|ai}}  as ''≈õuddha'' {{angle bracket|ayi}}.

Note that the transliteration of both ‡∑Ö‡∑ä and ‡∑ü is {{angle bracket|·∏∑}}. This is not very problematic as the second one is extremely scarce.
{{clear}}

